Rggml builds a selected GGML engine into inst/ggml/libggml.a and exposes a
narrow C-callable API. This notice records the source, retained licenses and
first-party integration code.

Upstream GGML
-------------
Project: https://github.com/ggml-org/ggml
Copyright: Georgi Gerganov and contributors
License: MIT

The generated source tree is selected from official tag v0.11.0, commit
1f09c6987071512f9a11189880c0130b1349b8dc. The 487 selected paths and contents
have tree sha256
e2b4e65f0780bfe14884d924649a68b4b2d3326cbb9644046fa6e3f13dbb8ea9.
`tools/vendor-ggml/vendorggml.R` verifies that digest before copying anything.

The selection contains the tensor and graph core, allocator, backend registry,
official GGUF reader and writer, tensor-level quantization, portable CPU
backend, BLAS backend, aarch64 quantized kernels, Vulkan backend and shader
sources, CUDA backend, and their public headers. All remain under GGML's MIT
license.

The repository's patches adapt internal interfaces for Windows MinGW, preserve
driver-backed objects across process teardown, guard failed context-pool
allocations, connect Rggml's runtime q4_K dispatcher, permit opt-in Vulkan CPU
devices for CI, and make GGML's format attributes compatible with the R-safe
I/O redirection. These modifications remain derivative GGML code under MIT.

R integration overlay
---------------------
`inst/ggml/rggml_compat.h` and `inst/ggml/rggml_io.c` are adapted from ggmlR's
R compatibility shim by Yuri Baramykov. They redirect direct console and
process-termination calls through R's API. They remain under ggmlR's MIT
license, reproduced below. No GGML engine source is taken from ggmlR.

`inst/ggml/cblas.h` and `inst/ggml/rggml_cblas.c` bridge GGML's CBLAS call to
R's guaranteed Fortran BLAS interface. The static-library Makefile, configure
integration, Rggml C-callable layer, R code and tests are Rggml code under GPL
(>= 2).

Runtime SIMD dispatch
---------------------
`tools/simd/cpu_features.c` and `tools/simd/cpu_features.h` come from the
RsimdDispatch package by the same author and remain under GPL (>= 2).
`tools/simd/rggml_simd_dispatch.c` is Rggml code under GPL (>= 2).
`tools/simd/vec_dot_q4_K.c` contains a GGML-derived q4_K dot body under MIT and
Rggml dispatch integration under GPL (>= 2).

The MIT components are GPL-compatible. Their copyright notices and permission
terms are preserved here and are not relicensed by the package's GPL
declaration.

